00:01:52.750 --> 00:01:56.780
ends showing in my hair. Ok and now to the
hairstyle, so you're going to need to part

00:01:56.780 --> 00:02:01.870
your hair at the side, just above your ear,
take a section of hair round the back of your

00:02:01.870 --> 00:02:07.450
ear a couple of inches thick and then brush
that to make sure it's really nice and neat

00:02:07.450 --> 00:02:11.480
so you've got all the hair in there. And then
you're just going to do a simple plait with

00:02:11.480 --> 00:02:16.290
that hair. Obviously the more hair you have,
the thicker your plait is going to be. Now

00:02:16.290 --> 00:02:20.170
I wanted to do a hairstyle that's just very
easy wearable so don't worry about this being

00:02:20.170 --> 00:02:24.969
too neat. It's designed to be a little bit
of a messier kind of half up do. And then

00:02:24.969 --> 00:02:29.420
just take the bits of the plaits and pull
slightly to make the plait nice and chunky

00:02:29.420 --> 00:02:33.090
and give you some extra volume. Take it over
to the other side and then you're going to

00:02:33.090 --> 00:02:37.260
grip that in place with a couple of pins and
do exactly the same with the other side as

00:02:37.260 --> 00:02:42.029
well. Then you're going to get a section at
the back and comb it and then back comb it

00:02:42.029 --> 00:02:46.829
just to give you a little bit of volume. Take
that hair at the back, twist it a couple of

00:02:46.829 --> 00:02:52.650
times and then you're going to pin that in
place as well. This is just giving you a little

00:02:52.650 --> 00:02:57.439
bit of volume and neatening it up at the back.
So put that in place again with a couple of

00:02:57.439 --> 00:03:02.230
grips. Then I'm going to use my Sebastian
Trilliant Heat Protection Spray, shake this

00:03:02.230 --> 00:03:05.659
really well before you put it on and then
just spray that on. I am going to put hot

00:03:05.659 --> 00:03:11.079
irons on my hair, so I don't want it to burn.
And then I'm using my Jose Eber curling wand,

00:03:11.079 --> 00:03:17.469
this is a 35mm barrel, nice and big, just
to give me a couple of curls at the front

00:03:17.469 --> 00:03:23.120
as well. Then I'm going to take my Caviar
working hair spray just to keep this all in

00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:26.959
place and again you're going to do the same
thing to the other side. I actually take a

00:03:26.959 --> 00:03:30.719
